@startuml C4_Quality_CodeReview
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Quality Gate - Code Review Process

Boundary(submission, "Submission Phase") {
    Component(developer, "Developer", "Author", "Submits PR")
    Component(auto_checks, "AutomaticChecks", "CI", "Run tests/lint")
    Component(pr_description, "PRDescription", "Metadata", "What/why/how")
}

Boundary(review_criteria, "Review Criteria") {
    Component(design_review, "DesignReview", "Architecture", "Follows patterns")
    Component(security_review, "SecurityReview", "Safety", "No vulnerabilities")
    Component(perf_review, "PerformanceReview", "Efficiency", "Not slower")
    Component(test_review, "TestReview", "Coverage", "80%+ coverage")
    Component(doc_review, "DocumentationReview", "Clarity", "Updated docs")
}

Boundary(approval_path, "Approval Path") {
    Component(junior_review, "JuniorReview", "First", "Code quality")
    Component(senior_review, "SeniorReview", "Second", "Design/architecture")
    Component(security_review_final, "SecurityReview (Final)", "Gating", "Security gate")
    Component(merge_ready, "MergeReady", "Gate", "Approved")
}

Boundary(feedback_resolution, "Feedback Resolution") {
    Component(comments, "Comments", "Feedback", "GitHub comments")
    Component(conversations, "Conversations", "Debate", "Thread discussions")
    Component(revisions, "Revisions", "Iteration", "Address feedback")
    Component(re_review, "ReReview", "Validation", "Verify fixes")
}

submission --> auto_checks: Triggers
auto_checks --> pr_description: Checks
pr_description --> design_review: Sent to
design_review --> security_review: Then
security_review --> test_review: Then
test_review --> junior_review: First reviewer
junior_review --> senior_review: If approved
senior_review --> security_review_final: If approved
security_review_final --> merge_ready: If approved
merge_ready --> comments: Issues found?
comments --> conversations: Discusses
conversations --> revisions: Developer fixes
revisions --> re_review: Re-review cycle

Note as N1
Code Review Process:

Submission:
1. Developer submits PR with description
2. CI runs: tests, linting, coverage
3. PR description explains what/why/how

Review Checklist:
- Design: Follows architecture patterns
- Security: No vulnerabilities (OWASP)
- Performance: Not slower than baseline
- Testing: 80%+ code coverage
- Documentation: Updated/accurate

Approval Workflow:
1. Junior Review (first): Code quality, tests
   - Approval: ✅
   - Changes requested: Resubmit
2. Senior Review (second): Design, architecture
   - Approval: ✅
   - Changes requested: Resubmit
3. Security Review (gating): Vulnerability scan
   - Approval: ✅
   - Changes requested: Resubmit
4. Merge Ready: All approvals + CI green

Feedback Loop:
1. Reviewers add comments
2. Developer discusses in threads
3. Developer makes revisions
4. Request re-review
5. Reviewers verify fixes
6. Approve and merge

SLA:
- First review: <4 hours
- Follow-up reviews: <2 hours
- Developer response: <4 hours
- Merge: <24 hours from approval

Merge Criteria:
- ✅ All tests GREEN
- ✅ Coverage ≥80%
- ✅ Guards (H) GREEN
- ✅ Invariants (Q) GREEN
- ✅ 2+ approvals (junior + senior)
- ✅ Security review approved
- ✅ No unresolved conversations

Common Rejection Reasons:
1. No test coverage (too risky)
2. Breaking API change (undocumented)
3. Performance regression (>10% slower)
4. Security vulnerability (CVE)
5. Code duplication (DRY violation)
6. Missing documentation
7. Architecture deviation
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
